    <string name="about_title">Owl SMS</string>
    <string name="about_intro">
        This application makes requests directly to the Twilio services to send, receive, and manage messages; and retrieve the account\'s list of SMS capable phone numbers.
        \n
    </string>

    <string name="about_asis">
        Owl SMS is offered \"as is\", without warranty or guarantee.
    </string>
    <string name="about_version">
        \nVersion: 2.0
        \nRelease date: November 18, 2017
        \n
        \nThis application is not a Twilio company application, even though it was developed by Twilio employees. There is a saying within the company, "Just draw the Owl." This is our drawing of an SMS application.
    </string>
    <!-- \n Draw the Owl: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dwSe2imUyvg -->

    <!-- ======================================================================================= -->
    <string name="about_twiliosetup">
        Twilio Account Setup
    </string>
    <string name="about_twilioaccount">
        To use Owl SMS, you are required to have a Twilio account with at least one SMS capable phone number.
        \n
        \nGo to http://Twilio.com/console to get and manage your account.
        \n
        \nThe account SID and auth token is located on the page when you first log in.
        \n
        \nYou can use a free Twilio Trial account with Owl SMS, however, take note of the restrictions. For example, you can only send and receive messages, to and from, phone numbers you have pre-verified. For more information, search for \"How does Twilio\'s Free Trial work?\"
    </string>
    <string name="about_noresponse_title">
        Remove the SMS Automatic Reply
    </string>
    <string name="about_noresponse">
        \nBy default a Twilio phone number is configured with an automatic reply which you will want to stop.
    \n
    \n1. In the Twilio Console, go to managing phone numbers:
    \nhttps://www.twilio.com/console/phone-numbers/incoming
        \n
    \n2. Click your phone number.
        \nNote: Messaging, A MESSAGE COMES IN, is set to: Webhook.
        \nChange, Webhook to TwiML.
        \nNow, to the right is a circle icon with a plus sign in the middle.
        \nClick the icon.
        \nIn the New TwiML Bin popup form, enter:
        \nFriendly Name: NoSmsResponse
        \nBelow, in the codebox, enter the following TwiML:
        \n&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?&gt;
        \n&lt;Response/&gt;
        \n
        \nBelow the codebox, is the message, Valid TwiML.
        \n
        \n3. Click Create. The popup form disappears.
        \n
    \n4. Click Save.
    \n
        \nNow, when a message is sent to your Twilio phone number, there is no automatic reply.
    </string>

